What version of Heritrix are you using? 1.12.1 has fixes that would be 
relevant to your launching of many crawls in the same JVM invocation 
(especially HER-1120 and HER-1121), so please try it if you're not 
already using it.

Also remember that every crawl creates its own BerkeleyDB-JE 
environment, and each such environment tries to limit its cache by 
default to using 60% of the total heap. So, if you leave this default in 
place, and launch 2 simultaneous crawls, their environments will seek to 
limit themselves to 120% of the heap -- almost guaranteed to cause 
problems unless the crawls wrap up very quickly.

The "gc overhead limit exceeded" message suggests to me that you're 
using Java 1.6. (Previous versions didn't give that much detail.) Is 
that the case? An interesting thing about this error is that it does not 
indicate there was insufficient memory for an allocation -- only that GC 
was taking so much time that the system decided to give up.

The size and number of 'settings'-related instances in your 'jmap 
-histo' output caught my eye. Are you making extensive use of per-domain 
overrides?

- Gordon @ IA
